Since δL depends only on v, the expression must be independent of r and t. Therefore, we must have ∇ᵣF = g (constant) and ∂F/∂t = 0. Then δL(v) = ⟨g, v⟩. The condition δL(0) = 0 implies g = 0, so δL(v) = 0, which is trivially linear.

